[[File:Teatro Comunale Alessandro Bonci.jpg|thumb|Teatro Comunale Alessandro Bonci]] [[File:Interno Teatro Bonci.jpg|thumb|Interior view]]
The '''Teatro Comunale Alessandro Bonci''' (''Alessandro Bonci Theatre'') is an [[opera house]] in [[Cesena]], Italy.<ref>[http://www.beniculturali.it/mibac/opencms/MiBAC/sito-MiBAC/Luogo/MibacUnif/Luoghi-della-Cultura/visualizza_asset.html?id=155623&pagename=57 Teatro Alessandro Bonci], Ministero dei beni e delle attività culturali e del turismo</ref> [[File:Paolo Monti - Servizio fotografico (Cesena, 1972) - BEIC 6347401.jpg|thumb|upright|Detail of the facade. Photo by [[Paolo Monti]], 1972.]]
The Bonci Theatre was built on the site of the old ''Spada Theatre'' starting in August 1843 on a design by the architect Vincenzo Ghinelli and was opened on 15 August 1846.
It distinguished itself immediately with the best dramatic and lyric opera productions, a fact confirmed by the presence of leading performers of the period. It was dedicated to the great [[tenor]] from [[Cesena]] [[Alessandro Bonci]] after his performances of 1904 and 1927.
The theater is a member of the Italian route section of the [[European Route of Historic Theatres]].<ref>[http://www.perspectiv-online.org/pages/en/bull-italian-route.php European Route of Historic Theatres] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131110021620/http://www.perspectiv-online.org/pages/en/bull-italian-route.php |date=2013-11-10 }}</ref>
